Although some people
might be able to do it,

02:17:11.800 --> 02:17:15.370
maybe you and your family or
your friends, your, you know,

02:17:15.370 --> 02:17:16.861
you're eating a late breakfast or a,

02:17:16.861 --> 02:17:20.170
and then you're having a
late-ish lunch around 2:00 PM.

02:17:20.170 --> 02:17:21.480
And then you have dinner at six.

02:17:21.480 --> 02:17:25.110
And then assuming that you
go to bed around nine 30 or

02:17:25.110 --> 02:17:26.080
10:00 PM,

02:17:26.080 --> 02:17:30.956
that is going to extract
the maximum amount of weight

02:17:30.956 --> 02:17:35.956
related body fat related metabolic
factor related aspects of

02:17:37.590 --> 02:17:39.600
time, restricted feeding.

02:17:39.600 --> 02:17:43.261
Some people tend to fall into
a category where they do best

02:17:43.261 --> 02:17:47.436
placing that feeding window
later in the day and provided

02:17:47.436 --> 02:17:49.700
it. Doesn't run too close to your sleep.

02:17:49.700 --> 02:17:51.790
Remember you needed a two or
three hour buffer before your

02:17:51.790 --> 02:17:52.623
sleep,

02:17:52.623 --> 02:17:54.940
where you're not ingesting
anything that's in order to

02:17:54.940 --> 02:17:57.197
extract the benefits of
time-restricted feeding.

02:17:57.197 --> 02:18:02.090
Well then starting your
feeding window at 12:00 PM and

02:18:02.090 --> 02:18:06.237
ending at 8:00 PM plus or
minus half an hour or so day to

02:18:06.237 --> 02:18:09.720
day, it seems like a perfectly
reasonable schedule for some

02:18:09.720 --> 02:18:12.021
people starting at 2:00 PM
and ending at 10:00 PM will be

02:18:12.021 --> 02:18:13.641
